om host to host. The concise entries that follow highlight important or interesting facts about each virus. Learn about the geographic origins of dengue and why old tires and unused pots help the virus to spread. Read about Ebola, Zika, West Nile, Frog virus 3, the Tulip breaking virus, and many others-how they were discovered, what their hosts are, how they are transmitted, whether or not there is a vaccine, and much more. Each entry is easy to read and includes a graphic of the virus, and nearly every entry features a colorized image of the virus as seen through the microscope.Written by a leading authority, this handsomely illustrated guide reveals the unseen wonders of the microbial world. It will give you an entirely new appreciation for viruses.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aViruses. 7aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Virology.2bisacsh  acoronavirus.1 aZimmer, Carl.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311063859240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781400883257zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781400883257423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781400883257.jpg  a978-3-11-063859-2  Princeton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK